(102, NULL, 18, 1, '<p>$$ \\text { Differentiate } f(x)=x^2-3 x \\text { from first principles } $$</p>\r\n\r\n<p>[2 marks]</p>', 'Quiz', 5, 5, 7, '<p>Recalling the first principles formula: $$ f^{\\prime}(x)=\\lim _{h \\rightarrow 0} \\frac{f(x+h)-f(x)}{h} $$ Since \\(f(x)=x^2-3 x\\)&nbsp;$$ \\begin{aligned} f(x+h) &amp; =(x+h)^2-3(x+h) \\\\ &amp; =x^2+2 x h+h^2-3 x-3 h \\end{aligned} $$ Substituting this into the formula: $$ \\begin{aligned} \\therefore f^{\\prime}(x) &amp; =\\lim _{h \\rightarrow 0} \\frac{\\left(x^2+2 x h+h^2-3 x-3 h\\right)-\\left(x^2-3 x\\right)}{h} \\\\ &amp; =\\lim _{h \\rightarrow 0} \\frac{x^2+2 x h+h^2-3 x-3 h-x^2+3 x}{h} \\\\ &amp; =\\lim _{h \\rightarrow 0} \\frac{2 x h+h^2-3 h}{h} \\\\ &amp; =\\lim _{h \\rightarrow 0} \\frac{h(2 x+h-3)}{h} \\\\ &amp; =\\lim _{h \\rightarrow 0}(2 x+h-3) \\end{aligned} $$ Then finally applying our limit: $$ \\begin{gathered} \\therefore \\lim _{h \\rightarrow 0}(2 x+h-3)=2 x-3 \\\\ \\therefore f^{\\prime}(x)=2 x-3 \\end{gathered} $$</p>', 'correct', '<p>$$2x-3$$</p>', '180', 'Hard', '2', 1, NULL, '2024-03-24 11:40:57', '2024-03-19 16:42:30'),
