(108, NULL, 19, 1, '<p>A function is given by \\(f(x)=2 x^2+3 x\\)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>i. Determine whether the function is odd, even or neither, providing reasoning for your answer&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>[2 marks]</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nii. Show that \\(f(x+h)=2 x^2+4 x h+2 h^2+3 x+3 h\\)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>[1 mark]</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\niii. Hence, find \\(f^{\\prime}(x)\\) from first principles</p>\r\n\r\n<p>[2 marks]</p>', 'Quiz', 5, 5, 7, '<p>i. Determining the expression for \\(f(-x)\\) : $$ \\begin{aligned} f(-x) &amp; =2(-x)^2+3(-x) \\\\ &amp; =2 x^2-3 x \\end{aligned} $$ Determining the expression for \\(-f(x)\\): $$ \\begin{aligned} -f(x) &amp; =-\\left(2 x^2+3 x\\right) \\\\ &amp; =-2 x^2-3 x \\end{aligned} $$ Since \\(f(x) \\neq f(-x), f(x)\\) is NOT even&nbsp;<br />\r\nSince \\(f(-x) \\neq-f(x), f(x)\\) is NOT odd&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nHence, we can determine that \\(f(x)\\) is neither even nor odd</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ii. Since \\(f(x)=2 x^2+3 x\\) : $$ \\begin{aligned} \\therefore f(x+h) &amp; =2(x+h)^2+3(x+h) \\\\ &amp; =2\\left(x^2+2 x h+h^2\\right)+3 x+3 h \\\\ &amp; =2 x^2+4 x h+2 h^2+3 x+3 h \\end{aligned} $$</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>iii. Substituting our expressions for \\(f(x)\\) and \\(f(x+h)\\) into the first principles formula in order to simplify our expression and cancel out the \\(h\\) on the denominator: $$ \\begin{aligned} f^{\\prime}(x) &amp; =\\lim _{h \\rightarrow 0} \\frac{f(x+h)-f(x)}{h} \\\\ &amp; =\\lim _{h \\rightarrow 0} \\frac{\\left(2 x^2+4 x h+2 h^2+3 x+3 h\\right)-\\left(2 x^2+3 x\\right)}{h} \\\\ &amp; =\\lim _{h \\rightarrow 0} \\frac{2 x^2+4 x h+2 h^2+3 x+3 h-2 x^2-3 x}{h} \\\\ &amp; =\\lim _{h \\rightarrow 0} \\frac{4 x h+2 h^2+3 h}{h} \\\\ &amp; =\\lim _{h \\rightarrow 0} \\frac{h(4 x+2 h+3)}{h} \\\\ &amp; =\\lim _{h \\rightarrow 0}(4 x+2 h+3) \\end{aligned} $$ Finally, applying our limit: $$ \\begin{gathered} \\lim _{h \\rightarrow 0}(4 x+2 h+3)=4 x+3 \\\\ \\therefore f^{\\prime}(x)=4 x+3 \\end{gathered} $$</p>', 'correct', '<p>part i:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">Neither</p>\r\n\r\n<p>part ii:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">Answer is shown</p>\r\n\r\n<p>part iii:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>$$f&#39;(x)=4x+3$$</p>', '600', 'Medium', '5', 1, NULL, '2024-03-19 16:51:38', '2024-03-19 16:51:38'),
