(153, NULL, 29, 1, '<p>$$ \\text { Given that } f(x)=(3 x-5)^4 \\text {, what is the expression for } f^{\\prime}(x) \\text { ? } $$</p>\r\n\r\n<p>[1 mark]</p>', 'Quiz', 5, 5, 9, '<p>Solution: Recalling the chain rule:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If \\(f(x)=(a x+b)^n\\), then \\(f^{\\prime}(x)=a \\cdot n(a x+b)^{n-1}\\)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Then therefore: $$ \\begin{aligned} f^{\\prime}(x) &amp; =3 \\cdot 4(3 x-5)^{4-1} \\\\ &amp; =12(3 x-5)^3 \\\\ &amp;&nbsp; \\end{aligned} $$</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>\\(4(3 x-5)^3\\)</p>', '60', 'Medium', '1', 1, NULL, '2024-03-24 11:36:12', '2024-03-19 19:12:05'),
