(157, NULL, 30, 1, '<p>$$ \\text { If } y=x^3(x-2)^2, \\text { then } \\frac{d y}{d x}=&nbsp;? $$</p>\r\n\r\n<p>[1 mark]</p>', 'Both', 5, 5, 9, '<p>Solution: Using the product rule \\((u v)^{\\prime}=u^{\\prime} v+v^{\\prime} u\\): $$ \\begin{aligned} \\left(x^3(x-2)^2\\right)^{\\prime} &amp; =\\left(x^3\\right)^{\\prime}(x-2)^2+\\left((x-2)^2\\right)^{\\prime} x^3 \\\\ &amp; =3 x^2(x-2)^2+2(x-2) x^3 \\\\ &amp; =3 x^2(x-2)^2+2 x^3(x-2) \\\\ &amp; =x^2(x-2)(3(x-2)+2x) \\\\ &amp; =x^2(x-2)(3 x-6+2x) \\\\ &amp; =x^2(x-2)(5&nbsp;x-6) \\end{aligned} $$</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>\\(3 x^2(x-2)^2\\)</p>', '120', 'Medium', '1', 1, NULL, '2024-03-24 11:36:21', '2024-03-19 19:13:28'),
