(173, NULL, 34, 1, '<p>$$ \\text { For the function } f(x)=\\left(x^3+x\\right)^4 \\text {, which of the following is } f^{\\prime}(x) \\text { ? } $$</p>\r\n\r\n<p>[1 mark]</p>', 'Quiz', 5, 5, 9, '<p>Solution: Doing this question by substitution: Let \\(u=x^3+x\\): $$ \\begin{gathered} \\frac{d u}{d x}=3 x^2+1 \\\\ y=f(x)=u^4 \\\\ \\frac{d y}{d u}=4 u^3 \\end{gathered} $$ Hence, by the chain rule: $$ \\begin{aligned} \\frac{d y}{d x} &amp; =\\frac{d y}{d u} \\times \\frac{d u}{d x} \\\\ &amp; =4 u^3 \\times\\left(3 x^2+1\\right) \\\\ &amp; =4\\left(3 x^2+1\\right) u^3 \\\\ &amp; =4\\left(3 x^2+1\\right)\\left(x^3+x\\right)^3 \\end{aligned} $$</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>$$4\\left(3 x^2+1\\right)^3$$</p>', '120', 'Medium', '1', 1, NULL, '2024-03-24 11:37:04', '2024-03-19 19:21:03'),
