(185, NULL, 37, 1, '<p>Which of the following is the gradient of the tangent to \\(y=x^3-x^2+1\\)&nbsp;when the \\(x -\\)coordinate is 3?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>[1 mark]</p>', 'Quiz', 5, 5, 10, '<p>Solution:<br />\r\nFor tangent questions, we first differentiate \\(y\\)&nbsp;to find \\(y^{\\prime}\\): $$ y^{\\prime}=3 x^2-2 x $$ Then, finding the gradient of the tangent when \\(x=3\\)&nbsp;by substituting into \\(y^{\\prime}\\): $$ \\begin{aligned} m &amp; =3(3)^2-2(3) \\\\ &amp; =27-6 \\\\ &amp; =21 \\end{aligned} $$</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>\\(3\\)</p>', '120', 'Medium', '1', 1, NULL, '2024-03-24 11:33:36', '2024-03-19 19:40:04'),
