(189, NULL, 38, 1, '<p>$$ \\text { For the function } f(x)=2 e^x \\text {, what is the gradient of the normal to the point }(1,2 e) \\text { ? } $$</p>', 'Exam Builder', 5, 10, NULL, '<p>Solution:<br />\r\nFor tangent questions, we first differentiate $f(x)$ to find $f^{\\prime}(x)$ : $$ f^{\\prime}(x)=2 e^x $$ Then, finding the gradient of the tangent when $x=1$ : $$ m_t=f^{\\prime}(1)=2 e^1 $$ Hence, the gradient of the normal to the point will be the negative reciprocal: $$ \\begin{aligned} m_n &amp; =-\\frac{1}{m_t} \\\\ &amp; =-\\frac{1}{2 e} \\\\ &amp; =-\\frac{1}{2} e^{-1} \\end{aligned} $$</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>$$ \\frac{1}{2} e^1 $$</p>', '120', 'Medium', '1', 1, NULL, '2024-03-19 19:41:14', '2024-03-19 19:41:14'),
