(197, NULL, 40, 1, '<p>$$ \\text { At what angle is the line } y=-\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}} x+2 \\text { inclined to the positive side of the } x-\\text { axis? } $$</p>\r\n\r\n<p>[1 mark]</p>', 'Quiz', 5, 5, 10, '<p>Solution:<br />\r\nSince the line is in the form \\(y=m x+b\\), the gradient of the line is:<br />\r\n$$<br />\r\nm=-\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}}<br />\r\n$$</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Then, using the equation \\(m=\\tan \\theta\\) to find the angle:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>$$<br />\r\n-\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}}=\\tan \\theta<br />\r\n$$</p>\r\n\r\n<p>$$<br />\r\n\\begin{aligned}<br />\r\n\\therefore \\theta &amp; =180^{\\circ}-30^{\\circ}[2 \\text { nd quadrant angle } \\because \\tan \\theta&lt;0] \\\\<br />\r\n&amp; =150^{\\circ}<br />\r\n\\end{aligned}<br />\r\n$$</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>\\(30^{\\circ}\\)</p>', '120', 'Medium', '1', 1, NULL, '2024-03-24 11:34:00', '2024-03-19 19:54:27'),
