(208, NULL, 43, 1, '<p>$$ \\text { Find the equation of the tangent to the curve } y=2 x^3-x+3 \\text { at } x=1 $$</p>\r\n\r\n<p>[2 marks]</p>', 'Quiz', 5, 5, 10, '<p>Solution:<br />\r\nFor tangent questions, we differentiate first: $$ y^{\\prime}=6 x^2-1 $$ When \\(x=1\\), the gradient is: $$ m=6(1)^2-1=5 $$ When \\(x=1, y=2(1)^3-1+3=4\\)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Finally using the point - gradient formula to find the equation of the tangent: $$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; y-y_1=m\\left(x-x_1\\right) \\\\ &amp; y-4=5(x-1) \\\\ &amp; y-4=5 x-5 \\\\ &amp; \\therefore y=5 x-1 \\end{aligned} $$</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>\\(y=3x+2\\)</p>', '180', 'Medium', '2', 1, NULL, '2024-03-24 11:34:44', '2024-03-19 19:59:36'),
