(214, NULL, 44, 1, '<p>The graph of \\(y=f(x)\\)&nbsp;is shown below. For which interval is \\(f^{\\prime}(x)&gt;0\\)?</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img src=\"https://lwfiles.mycourse.app/63869eb3262971b3f737797c-public/e2ef57900bbbc36472aa5062bf60e6c5.png\" style=\"height:263px; width:500px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>[1 mark]</p>', 'Quiz', 5, 5, 11, '<p>Solution:<br />\r\nSince we are looking for when \\(f^{\\prime}(x)&gt;0\\), this is when the graph is increasing.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nNotice that the graph is increasing when \\(x&lt;-2\\)&nbsp;and when \\(x&gt;4\\).<br />\r\n<br />\r\nHence, in interval notation this may be expressed as: $$ (-\\infty,-2) \\cup(4, \\infty) $$</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>\\((-4.6,2.2)\\)</p>', '120', 'Medium', '1', 1, NULL, '2024-03-24 11:32:25', '2024-03-20 06:41:18'),
