(240, NULL, 49, 1, '<p>A large fishbowl which contains \\(L\\) litres of dirty fish water is being drained. The amount of water in the bowl after \\(t\\) minutes is given by: $$ L=50(15-t)^2 $$</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;i. At what rate is the water draining out of the fishbowl after 6 minutes? &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>[2 marks]&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nii. How long until the tank is completely empty?&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>[1 mark]</p>', 'Quiz', 5, 5, 12, '<p>i. To find the rate of drainage, differentiate first: $$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; L=50\\left(225-30 t+t^2\\right) \\\\ &amp; L=11250-1500 t+50 t^2 \\\\ &amp; L^{\\prime}=-1500+100 t \\end{aligned} $$ When \\(t=6\\), finding the value of \\(L^{\\prime}\\): $$ \\begin{aligned} L^{\\prime} &amp; =-1500+100(6) \\\\ &amp; =-900 \\end{aligned} $$ Hence, the rate that the water is draining out when \\(t=6\\) is \\(900 \\mathrm{~L} / \\mathrm{min}\\)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nii. For \\(L=0\\): $$ L=50(15-t)^2=0 $$ This occurs when \\(t=15\\). Hence, it takes 15 minutes for the tank to be empty</p>', 'correct', '<p>part i:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">\\(900\\)&nbsp;litres per minute</p>\r\n\r\n<p>part ii:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">\\(15\\) minutes</p>', '300', 'Hard', '3', 1, NULL, '2024-03-20 09:37:25', '2024-03-20 09:37:25'),
