(252, NULL, 51, 1, '<p>The displacement of an object \\(x\\) metres from the origin after \\(t\\) seconds is given by the expression: $$ x=t^2-6 t+5 $$ When 3 seconds has passed, what is the object&#39;s displacement?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>[1 mark]</p>', 'Quiz', 5, 5, 13, '<p>Letting \\(t=3\\): $$ \\begin{aligned} x &amp; =(3)^2-6(3)+5 \\\\ &amp; =9-18+5 \\\\ &amp; =-9+5 \\\\ &amp; =-4 \\end{aligned} $$ Hence, the displacement here is \\(-4 m\\)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Note that for this question, we are asked for displacement. Hence, since displacement has a direction, our answer must include a negative sign!</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>\\(4\\)</p>', '60', 'Easy', '1', 1, NULL, '2024-03-24 11:35:12', '2024-03-20 09:47:19'),
