(260, NULL, 53, 1, '<p>An object&#39;s displacement measured in \\(x\\) metres after \\(t\\) seconds is given by the equation: $$ x=2 t^3+3 t^2-t+5 $$ Which of the following is the expression for the acceleration of this object?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>[1 mark]</p>', 'Quiz', 5, 5, 13, '<p>First, differentiating \\(x\\) to find the velocity equation: $$ v=\\frac{d x}{d t}=6 t^2+6 t-1 $$ Then differentiating again to find the acceleration equation: $$ a=\\frac{d v}{d t}=\\frac{d^2 x}{d t^2}=12 t+6 $$ Hence, the expression for acceleration is: $$ a=12 t+6 $$</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>\\(a=6t^2+6t-1\\)</p>', '120', 'Medium', '1', 1, NULL, '2024-03-24 11:35:33', '2024-03-20 09:50:17'),
