(266, NULL, 54, 3, '<p>A particle&#39;s velocity is given by the equation: $$ v=t^2-4 t-5 $$ Where \\(v\\) is the velocity of the particle and \\(t\\) is the time in seconds after the object begins moving&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At what time is the particle stationary?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>[1 mark]</p>', 'Both', 5, 5, 13, '<p>First, factorising our velocity equation: $$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; v=t^2-4 t-5 \\\\ &amp; v=(t-5)(t+1) \\end{aligned} $$ A particle is considered stationary when \\(v=0\\), hence: $$ t=5 \\text { or } t=-1 $$ However, \\(t&gt;0\\) so: $$ &nbsp;\\therefore t=5 \\text { ONLY } $$</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>\\(t=2\\)</p>', '120', 'Medium', '1', 1, NULL, '2024-03-24 11:35:44', '2024-03-20 09:52:37'),
