(366, NULL, 69, 1, '<p>A function is defined by: $$<br />\r\ny=\\cos ^2 \\sqrt{x-2}<br />\r\n$$ Which of the following gives the domain and range of this function?</p>', 'Quiz', 5, 7, 22, '<p>Solution:<br />\r\nIn regard to domain, the expression inside a square root cannot be negative, meaning that: $$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; x-2 \\geq 0 \\\\ &amp; \\therefore x \\geq 2 \\end{aligned} $$ For a cosine function: $$ \\begin{gathered} -1 \\leq \\cos \\theta \\leq 1 \\\\ \\therefore 0 \\leq \\cos ^2 \\theta \\leq 1 \\end{gathered} $$ Since \\(y=\\cos ^2 \\sqrt{x-2}\\), this therefore means that the range of the function is: $$ 0 \\leq y \\leq 1 $$</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>\\(x \\geq 0,-1 \\leq y \\leq 1\\)</p>', '120', 'Hard', '1', 1, NULL, '2024-03-24 08:44:31', '2024-03-24 08:44:31'),
