(370, NULL, 70, 1, '<p>$$ \\text { Which inequality defines the domain of the function } f(x)=\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{x+5}} \\text { ? } $$</p>', 'Quiz', 5, 7, 22, '<p>Solution:&nbsp;<br />\r\nSince an expression inside a square root cannot be negative: $$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\therefore x+5 \\geq 0 \\\\ &amp; x \\geq-5 \\end{aligned} $$ However, since the square root is on the denominator, it also cannot equal to 0 (we can&#39;t divide by 0 ) so we must change our domain to: $$ x&gt;-5 $$</p>', 'correct', '<p>\\(x&gt;-5\\)</p>', '60', 'Medium', '1', 1, NULL, '2024-03-24 08:46:52', '2024-03-24 08:46:52'),
