(411, NULL, 79, 4, '<p>$$ \\text { What is the range of } f(x)=4-x^2 ? $$</p>\r\n\r\n<p>[1 mark]</p>', 'Both', 5, 7, 24, '<p>Solution: The function \\(f(x)\\) is a concave down parabola (since we have anegative coefficient for \\(x^2\\) )</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Therefore, its vertex is the maximum point \\(x\\) - coordinate of vertex is: $$ -\\frac{b}{2 a}=-\\frac{0}{2(-1)}=0 $$ When \\(x=0, y=4-0^2=4\\)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Students may also quickly sketch the graph if they wish:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img src=\"https://lwfiles.mycourse.app/63869eb3262971b3f737797c-public/288c8a3162b2c065e3ccb9f82345d85f.png\" style=\"height:420px; width:395px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Therefore, maximum \\(y\\) - value is 4 , so the range of \\(f(x)\\) is \\(y \\leq 4\\) $$ \\therefore y \\in(-\\infty, 4] $$</p>', 'correct', '<p>\\((-\\infty, 4]\\)</p>', '120', 'Hard', '1', 1, NULL, '2024-03-24 11:27:58', '2024-03-24 16:16:25'),
(412, NULL, 80, 1, '<p>$$ \\text { What is the domain of the function } f(x)=\\ln (2-x)+\\sqrt{5 x-3} \\text { ? } $$</p>\r\n\r\n<p>[1 mark]</p>', 'Quiz', 5, 7, 24, '<p>Solution:<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor \\(\\ln (2-x)\\), since the expression inside a logarithm cannot be equal to 0 or negative: $$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; 2-x&gt;0 \\\\ &amp; \\therefore x&lt;2 \\end{aligned} $$ For \\(\\sqrt{5 x-3}\\), since we cannot square root a negative expression: $$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; 5 x-3 \\geq 0 \\\\ &amp; 5 x \\geq 3 \\\\ &amp; \\therefore x \\geq \\frac{3}{5} \\end{aligned} $$ Hence, combining these two domains together: $$ \\begin{gathered} \\therefore \\frac{3}{5} \\leq x&lt;2 \\\\ x \\in\\left[\\frac{3}{5}, 2\\right) \\end{gathered} $$</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>\\(x \\in\\left(\\frac{3}{5}, 2\\right)\\)</p>', '120', 'Hard', '1', 1, NULL, '2024-03-24 11:27:51', '2024-03-24 16:17:59'),
