(416, NULL, 81, 1, '<p>$$ \\text { Which interval gives the domain of the function } y=\\frac{3}{\\sqrt{x+6}} \\text { ? } $$</p>\r\n\r\n<p>[1 mark]</p>', 'Quiz', 5, 7, 24, '<p>Solution:<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSince an expression inside a square root cannot be negative: $$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\therefore x+6 \\geq 0 \\\\ &amp; x \\geq-6 \\end{aligned} $$ However, since the square root is on the denominator, it also cannot equal to 0 (we can&#39;t divide by 0), so we must change our domain to: $$ x&gt;-6 $$</p>', 'correct', '<p>\\((-6, \\infty)\\)</p>', '60', 'Medium', '1', 1, NULL, '2024-03-24 11:27:43', '2024-03-24 16:20:17'),
