(424, NULL, 83, 1, '<p>Which of the following is the equation of the line that has \\(y\\)-intercept at \\((0,6)\\) and is parallel to the line \\(y=-\\frac{3}{2} x+7 ?\\)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>[1 mark]</p>', 'Quiz', 5, 7, 25, '<p>Solution:&nbsp;<br />\r\nRecall that if a line is parallel to another, they have the same gradient $$ \\therefore m=-\\frac{3}{2} $$ Where \\(m\\) is the gradient of the unknown line. Moreover, recall the point - gradient equation of a line: $$ y=m x+b $$ Since it is known that the line has \\(y\\) - intercept at \\((0,6)\\) : $$ \\begin{gathered} \\therefore b=6 \\\\ \\therefore y=-\\frac{3}{2} x+6 \\end{gathered} $$</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>\\(y=\\frac{2}{3} x+6\\)</p>', '60', 'Easy', '1', 1, NULL, '2024-03-24 13:51:26', '2024-03-24 18:35:55'),
