(428, NULL, 84, 1, '<p>$$ \\text { Which of the following graphs best represents } y=x^2+4 x-5 \\text { ? } $$</p>', 'Quiz', 5, 7, 26, '<p>Solution:<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFirstly, since the coefficient of \\(x^2\\) is positive, the parabola is concave up&nbsp;<br />\r\nThen, factorising the quadratic to determine \\(x\\) - intercepts: $$ \\begin{gathered} y=x^2+4 x-5 \\\\ =(x+5)(x-1) \\\\ \\therefore x-\\text { intercepts at } x=-5, x=1 \\end{gathered} $$ Hence, the graph looks like:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img src=\"https://lwfiles.mycourse.app/63869eb3262971b3f737797c-public/9a3482b58e7272f7c5b58a7d17a8e7d0.png\" style=\"height:418px; width:319px\" /></p>', 'incorrect', '<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img src=\"https://lwfiles.mycourse.app/63869eb3262971b3f737797c-public/3f494cc76b022d8da54fb0d6a97bc55f.png\" /></p>', '120', 'Medium', '1', 1, NULL, '2024-03-24 18:37:36', '2024-03-24 18:37:36'),
