(444, NULL, 88, 1, '<p>$$ \\text { Which of the following is an even function? } $$</p>\r\n\r\n<p>[1 mark]</p>', 'Quiz', 5, 7, 28, '<p>Solution: An even function is defined algebraically as a function where: $$ f(x)=f(-x) $$ Now testing out each option:&nbsp;<br />\r\nIf \\(f(x)=x^2+x\\) $$ \\begin{aligned} f(-x) &amp; =(-x)^2+(-x) \\\\ &amp; =x^2-x \\\\ &amp; \\neq f(x) \\end{aligned} $$ Hence, not even<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIf \\(f(x)=x^3+x\\) $$ \\begin{aligned} f(-x) &amp; =(-x)^3+(-x) \\\\ &amp; =-x^3-x \\\\ &amp; \\neq f(x) \\end{aligned} $$ Hence, not even<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIf \\(f(x)=x^3+3\\) $$ \\begin{aligned} f(-x) &amp; =(-x)^3+3 \\\\ &amp; =-x^3+3 \\\\ &amp; \\neq f(x) \\end{aligned} $$ If \\(f(x)=x^2+3\\) $$ \\begin{aligned} f(-x) &amp; =(-x)^2+3 \\\\ &amp; =x^3+3 \\\\ &amp; =f(x) \\end{aligned} $$ Hence, this option is the even function and is thus the answer</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>\\(f(x)=x^2+x\\)</p>', '120', 'Hard', '1', 1, NULL, '2024-03-24 13:50:53', '2024-03-24 18:45:39'),
