(456, NULL, 91, 1, '<p>Given a function: $$f(x)=\\frac{2 x}{x^2-5}$$<br />\r\nWhich of the following statements is true?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>[1 mark]</p>', 'Quiz', 5, 7, 28, '<p>Solution:&nbsp;<br />\r\nIt appears that for \\(f(x)\\), many \\(x\\) - values correspond to only one \\(y\\)-value. Therefore, \\(f(x)\\) is considered many - to - one.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor example, for the \\(y\\) - value of 1 :$$ \\begin{gathered} 1=\\frac{2 x}{x^2-5} \\\\ x^2-5=2 x \\\\ x^2-2 x-5=0 \\\\ \\therefore x=\\frac{2 \\pm \\sqrt{4+20}}{2} \\end{gathered} $$ Hence, as can be seen, multiple \\(x\\) - values equal to the same one \\(y\\) - value. Now testing for even or odd, considering the expressions for \\(f(-x)\\) and \\(-f(x)\\) : $$ \\begin{aligned} f(-x) &amp; =\\frac{2(-x)}{(-x)^2-5} \\\\ &amp; =\\frac{-2 x}{x^2-5} \\\\ -f(x) &amp; =-\\frac{2 x}{x^2-5} \\\\ \\therefore f(-x) &amp; =-f(x) \\end{aligned} $$ Hence, \\(f(x)\\) is odd and many - to - one.</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>\\(f(x)\\) is even and one to one</p>', '60', 'Easy', '1', 1, NULL, '2024-03-24 18:50:45', '2024-03-24 18:50:45'),
