(466, NULL, 93, 1, '<p>$$ \\text { Let } f(x)=\\frac{2}{4-x} \\text { and } g(x)=x-3 \\text {. The domain of } f(g(x)) \\text { is: } $$</p>\r\n\r\n<p>[1 mark]</p>', 'Quiz', 5, 7, 29, '<p>Solution:&nbsp;<br />\r\nFirst, finding the equation for \\(f(g(x))\\) : $$ \\begin{aligned} f(g(x)) &amp; =\\frac{2}{4-(x-3)} \\\\ &amp; =\\frac{2}{4-x+3} \\\\ &amp; =\\frac{2}{7-x} \\end{aligned} $$ Since the denominator of a fraction cannot equal 0 , the only restriction is: $$ x \\neq 7 $$ Hence, the domain is all real \\(x, x \\neq 7\\)</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>all real \\(x\\)</p>', '120', 'Medium', '1', 1, NULL, '2024-03-24 18:57:58', '2024-03-24 18:57:58'),
