(474, NULL, 95, 1, '<p>It is known that \\(f(x)\\) is an odd function and \\(g(x)\\) is an even function. Given that \\(f(3)=3\\) and \\(g(3)=-3\\), what is the value of \\(f(g(-3))+g(f(-3))\\) ?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>[2&nbsp;marks]</p>', 'Both', 5, 7, 29, '<p>Solution:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Since \\(f(x)\\) is odd: $$f(-x)=-f(x)$$ $$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\therefore f(-3)=-f(3) \\\\ &amp; =-3 \\end{aligned} $$ Since \\(g(x)\\) is even: $$ g(x)=g(-x) $$$$ \\begin{aligned} \\therefore g(-3) &amp; =g(3) \\\\ &amp; =-3 \\\\ \\therefore f(g(-3))+g(f(-3)) &amp; =f(-3)+g(-3) \\\\ &amp; =-3+(-3) \\\\ &amp; =-6 \\end{aligned} $$ Hence, the answer is \\(-6\\)</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>\\(6\\)</p>', '180', 'Hard', '2', 1, NULL, '2024-03-24 14:02:18', '2024-03-24 18:59:51'),
