(492, NULL, 99, 1, '<p>$$ \\text { If } \\sin A=\\frac{3}{5} \\text { and } 0^{\\circ}&lt;A&lt;90^{\\circ}&nbsp;\\text { , which of the following represents the value of } \\cot A ?$$</p>', 'Quiz', 5, 29, 126, '<p>Since \\(\\sin A=\\frac{\\text { opposite }}{\\text { hypotenuse }}=\\frac{3}{5}\\), we can draw a right - angle triangle:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img src=\"https://lwfiles.mycourse.app/63869eb3262971b3f737797c-public/0374bb6c98aa54e29980275dc2e01a8a.jpeg\" style=\"height:167px; width:360px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>By Pythagoras theorem: $$ \\text { Adjacent side }=\\sqrt{5^2-3^2}=\\sqrt{16}=4 $$ Since \\(\\cot A=\\frac{\\text { adjacent }}{\\text { opposite }}\\) $$ \\therefore \\cot A=\\frac{4}{3} $$</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>\\(\\frac{3}{4}\\)</p>', '120', 'Medium', '1', 1, NULL, '2024-03-24 19:12:22', '2024-03-24 19:12:22'),
