(540, NULL, 108, 1, '<p>$$ \\text { Determine the size of angle } A \\text { in the following triangle: } $$</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img src=\"https://lwfiles.mycourse.app/63869eb3262971b3f737797c-public/33e42779bc6630dbe639a34a8d11c6c4.png\" style=\"height:370px; width:500px\" /></p>', 'Quiz', 5, 29, 128, '<p>Recalling the cosine rule: $$ c^2=a^2+b^2-2 a b \\cos \\theta $$ Rearranging to make \\(\\cos \\theta\\) the subject: $$ \\cos \\theta=\\frac{a^2+b^2-c^2}{2 a b} $$ Therefore, for this question: $$ \\begin{aligned} \\cos A &amp; =\\frac{10.2^2+11.8^2-12.1^2}{2 \\times 10.2 \\times 11.8} \\\\ &amp; =0.4024177468 \\\\ \\therefore A= &amp; 66^{\\circ} 16^{\\prime \\prime} \\text { (nearest minute) } \\end{aligned} $$</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>\\(59^{\\circ}44^{\\prime}\\)</p>', '120', 'Medium', '1', 1, NULL, '2024-03-25 15:02:37', '2024-03-25 15:02:37'),
