(544, NULL, 109, 1, '<p>Find the value of \\(x\\), correct to the nearest whole number</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img src=\"https://lwfiles.mycourse.app/63869eb3262971b3f737797c-public/21f4bf866ca1511b24b9413dbcb97dbb.png\" style=\"height:193px; width:500px\" /></p>', 'Both', 5, 29, 128, '<p>Recalling the cosine rule: $$ c^2=a^2+b^2-2 a b \\cos \\theta $$ Therefore, using the cosine rule for this question: $$ \\begin{aligned} x^2 &amp; =29^2+19^2-2 \\times 29 \\times 19 \\times \\cos 124^{\\circ} \\\\ &amp; =1818.23 \\\\ \\therefore x &amp; \\approx 43 \\mathrm{~cm} \\text { (nearest whole number) } \\end{aligned} $$</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>\\(x=39\\operatorname{cm}\\)</p>', '180', 'Medium', '2', 1, NULL, '2024-03-25 15:04:28', '2024-03-25 15:04:28'),
