(556, NULL, 111, 1, '<p>A circular clock face with centre \\(\\mathrm{O}\\), has a minute hand \\(\\mathrm{OA}\\) and an hour hand \\(\\mathrm{OB}\\). It is known that \\(OA=12 \\mathrm{~cm}\\) and \\(OB=9 \\mathrm{~cm}\\).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Calculate</strong> the length of \\(\\mathrm{AB}\\) when the hands show 4 o&#39;clock, giving your answer correct to 1 decimal place</p>', 'Quiz', 5, 29, 128, '<p>Since the clock is showing 4 o&#39;clock, we now know that \\(\\angle A O B=30^{\\circ} \\times 4=120^{\\circ}$&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nHence, considering the cosine rule: $$ \\begin{aligned} A B^2 &amp; =O A^2+O B^2-2(O A)(O B) \\cos \\angle A O B \\\\ &amp; =12^2+\\,9^2-2(12)(9) \\cos 120^{\\circ} \\\\ &amp; =333 \\\\ &amp; \\therefore A B \\approx 18.2 \\mathrm{~cm}[\\text {nearest } 1 \\text { d.p.}] \\end{aligned} $$</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>AB=33.3\\operatorname{cm}</p>', '180', 'Easy', '2', 1, NULL, '2024-03-25 15:14:35', '2024-03-25 15:14:35'),
