(562, NULL, 112, 1, '<p>In triangle \\(A B C: A B=13 \\mathrm{~cm}, B C=22 \\mathrm{~cm}\\) and \\(A C=26 \\mathrm{~cm}\\).&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">Find the exact area of the triangle&nbsp;</p>', 'Both', 5, 29, 128, '<p>Sketching a diagram first to help us visualise the problem:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img src=\"https://lwfiles.mycourse.app/63869eb3262971b3f737797c-public/3e431538faf2066ba48c970e660a56f3.png\" style=\"height:375px; width:500px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To calculate the area of this triangle, we aim to use the formula: $$ \\text { Area }=\\frac{1}{2} A B \\sin \\theta $$ Therefore, for this question: $$ \\text { Area } \\triangle A B C=\\frac{1}{2} \\times 13 \\times 26 \\times \\sin A $$ Notice that we need to first find angle \\(A\\) to apply this formula. Therefore, we use the cosine rule to try find the value of angle \\(A\\), where we recall that: $$ B C^2=A B^2+A C^2-2(A B)(A C) \\cos A $$Rearranging to make \\(\\cos A\\) the subject: $$ \\begin{aligned} \\therefore \\cos A &amp; =\\frac{A B^2+A C^2-B C^2}{2(A B)(A C)} \\\\ &amp; =\\frac{13^2+26^2-22^2}{2(13)(26)} \\\\ &amp; =\\frac{361}{676} \\end{aligned} $$ To find \\(\\sin A\\), we can use our calculator to find \\(A=\\cos ^{-1} \\frac{363}{676}\\) and then calculate \\(\\sin A\\) using the result, but a better way here (since we want exact) would be to sketch the right-angle triangle.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSince \\(\\cos A=\\frac{\\text { adjacent }}{\\text { hypotenuse }}=\\frac{361}{676}\\), we can sketch:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img src=\"https://lwfiles.mycourse.app/63869eb3262971b3f737797c-public/5b444f8b6b2eb5fe28497d049f923259.png\" style=\"height:356px; width:500px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Notice here that we have used Pythagoras to find the exact length of the opposite side: $$ \\begin{aligned} \\text { opposite length } &amp; =\\sqrt{676^2-361^2} \\\\ &amp; =\\sqrt{326655} \\end{aligned} $$ $$ \\therefore \\sin A=\\frac{\\text { opposite }}{\\text { hypotenuse }}=\\frac{\\sqrt{326655}}{676} $$ Substituting this back into our initial area formula: $$ \\begin{aligned} \\therefore \\text { Area } \\triangle A B C &amp; =\\frac{1}{2} \\times 13 \\times 26 \\times \\frac{\\sqrt{326655}}{676} \\\\ &amp; =\\frac{\\sqrt{326655}}{4} \\text { units }^2 \\end{aligned} $$ Note that any answer without surds will be deducted a mark! (since the question asked for exact area)</p>', 'correct', '<p>$$\\text { Area } \\triangle ABC=\\frac{\\sqrt{326655}}{4} \\text { units}^2$$</p>', '480', 'Hard', '3', 1, NULL, '2024-03-25 15:17:18', '2024-03-25 15:17:18'),
