 opposite }}{\\text { hypotenuse }}=\\frac{\\sqrt{326655}}{676} $$ Substituting this back into our initial area formula: $$ \\begin{aligned} \\therefore \\text { Area } \\triangle A B C &amp; =\\frac{1}{2} \\times 13 \\times 26 \\times \\frac{\\sqrt{326655}}{676} \\\\ &amp; =\\frac{\\sqrt{326655}}{4} \\text { units }^2 \\end{aligned} $$ Note that any answer without surds will be deducted a mark! (since the question asked for exact area)</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>$$\\text { Area } \\triangle ABC=\\frac{\\sqrt{309822}}{5} \\text { units}^2$$</p>', '480', 'Hard', '3', 1, NULL, '2024-03-25 15:17:18', '2024-03-25 15:17:18'),
