(595, NULL, 119, 1, '<p>$$ \\text {What is the perimeter } P \\text { of the sector given below with angle } 42^{\\circ} \\text { and radius } 15 \\mathrm{~cm} \\text { ? } $$</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img src=\"https://lwfiles.mycourse.app/63869eb3262971b3f737797c-public/a063ab9e8405036c2eb0d2bb4bfc25c0.png\" style=\"height:279px; width:241px\" /></p>', 'Quiz', 5, 29, 131, '<p>For the length of the straight edges: $$ 15+15=30 \\mathrm{~cm} $$ For the length of the curved edge: $$ l=r \\theta $$ Note however that \\(\\theta\\) must be in radians:&nbsp;$$ \\begin{aligned} 42^{\\circ} &amp; =42 \\times \\frac{\\pi}{180} \\\\ &amp; =\\frac{7 \\pi}{30} \\\\ \\therefore l &amp; =15 \\times \\frac{7 \\pi}{30} \\\\ &amp; =\\frac{7 \\pi}{2} \\mathrm{~cm} \\end{aligned} $$$$ \\therefore \\text { Total Perimeter }=30+\\frac{7 \\pi}{2} \\mathrm{~cm} $$</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>\\(\\frac{7 \\pi}{2} \\mathrm{~cm}\\)</p>', '120', 'Medium', '1', 1, NULL, '2024-03-26 18:06:32', '2024-03-26 18:06:32'),
