(599, NULL, 120, 1, '<p>$$ \\text { The area of a minor segment of a circle pictured below is } 50 \\pi \\text { metres squared. } $$</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img src=\"https://lwfiles.mycourse.app/63869eb3262971b3f737797c-public/f3edbd37c873b5d491244a0d8c395279.png\" style=\"height:237px; width:500px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>$$ \\text {Which of the following is the exact expression for the radius of the circle? } $$</p>', 'Both', 5, 29, 131, '<p>The area of a minor segment is given as: $$ \\begin{aligned} \\text { Area of Segment } &amp; =\\text { Area of Sector }- \\text { Area of Triangle } \\\\ &amp; =\\frac{1}{2} r^2 \\theta-\\frac{1}{2} r^2 \\sin \\theta \\\\ &amp; =\\frac{1}{2} r^2(\\theta-\\sin \\theta) \\end{aligned} $$ Hence, since the area of the segment in this case is \\(50 \\pi\\) and \\(\\theta=\\frac{\\pi}{3}\\): $$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; 50 \\pi=\\frac{1}{2} r^2\\left(\\frac{\\pi}{3}-\\sin \\frac{\\pi}{3}\\right) \\\\ &amp; 100 \\pi=r^2\\left(\\frac{\\pi}{3}-\\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2}\\right) \\end{aligned} $$$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; 100 \\pi=r^2\\left(\\frac{2 \\pi-3 \\sqrt{3}}{6}\\right) \\\\ &amp; r^2=100 \\pi \\times \\frac{6}{2 \\pi-3 \\sqrt{3}} \\\\ &amp; r^2=\\frac{600 \\pi}{2 \\pi-3 \\sqrt{3}} \\\\ &amp; \\therefore r=\\frac{10 \\sqrt{6 \\pi}}{\\sqrt{2 \\pi-3 \\sqrt{3}}} \\end{aligned} $$</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>\\(\\frac{10 \\sqrt{6 \\pi}}{\\sqrt{2 \\pi-1}}\\)</p>', '120', 'Hard', '1', 1, NULL, '2024-03-26 18:10:39', '2024-03-26 18:10:39'),
