(603, NULL, 121, 1, '<p>Kate has a backyard as shown in the diagram below by shape \\(\\mathrm{ABCD}\\). The sector \\(\\mathrm{BCD}\\) has a centre \\(\\mathrm{B}\\), and \\(A B=A D=4 \\mathrm{~m}\\).</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img src=\"https://lwfiles.mycourse.app/63869eb3262971b3f737797c-public/68fa1593f6ffa517d4ea67c154b634a6.png\" style=\"height:262px; width:500px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>i. Find the length of \\(\\mathrm{DB}\\)<br />\r\n[2 marks]</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ii. Find the total area of the backyard, leaving your answer in exact form&nbsp;<br />\r\n[2 marks]</p>', 'Quiz', 5, 29, 131, '<p>i. Considering \\(\\triangle A B D\\) and knowing that \\(\\angle D B A=\\pi-\\frac{5 \\pi}{6}=\\frac{\\pi}{6}\\).</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img src=\"https://lwfiles.mycourse.app/63869eb3262971b3f737797c-public/5e4d2e1bf7d34f27b7654daef2efe0b4.jpeg\" style=\"height:274px; width:340px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Since \\(\\triangle A B D\\) is isosceles, \\(\\angle A D B=\\frac{\\pi}{6}\\) (equal angles opposite equal sides) $$ \\therefore \\angle A D B=\\frac{2 \\pi}{3} $$ By the cosine rule: $$ \\begin{aligned} D B^2= &amp; \\,A D^2+A B^2-2(A D)(A B) \\cos \\angle D A B \\\\ = &amp; \\,4^2+4^2-2 \\times 4 \\times 4 \\times \\cos \\frac{2 \\pi}{3} \\\\ = &amp; \\,32-32\\left(-\\frac{1}{2}\\right) \\\\ = &amp; \\,48 \\\\ &amp; \\quad \\therefore D B=\\sqrt{48}=4 \\sqrt{3} \\mathrm{~m} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ii. The area of the backyard may be split into two parts, sector \\(\\mathrm{DBC}\\) and triangle DAB.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nFinding the area of sector DBC first: $$ \\begin{aligned} \\text { Sector Area } &amp; =\\frac{1}{2}r^2 \\theta \\\\ &amp; =\\frac{1}{2} \\times (4 \\sqrt{3})^2 \\times \\frac{5 \\pi}{6} \\\\ &amp; =\\frac{1}{2} \\times 48 \\times \\frac{5 \\pi}{6} \\\\ &amp; =20 \\pi \\mathrm{m}^2 \\end{aligned} $$ Then finding the area of \\(\\triangle D A B\\): $$ &nbsp;\\begin{aligned} &amp; \\triangle D A B=\\frac{1}{2} a b \\sin \\theta \\\\ &amp;=\\frac{1}{2} \\times(A B) \\times(A D) \\times \\sin \\angle D A B \\\\ &amp;=\\frac{1}{2} \\times 4 \\times 4 \\times \\sin \\frac{2 \\pi}{3} \\\\ &amp;=8 \\times \\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2} \\\\ &amp;=4 \\sqrt{3} \\mathrm{~m}^2 \\\\ &amp; \\therefore \\text { Total Area }=20 \\pi+4 \\sqrt{3} \\mathrm{~m}^2 \\end{aligned} $$</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>part i:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>$$DB=4\\sqrt{3} \\text{ m}$$</p>\r\n\r\n<p>part ii:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>$$\\text{Total Area }=40\\pi+4\\sqrt{3} \\text{ m}^2$$</p>', '420', 'Medium', '4', 1, NULL, '2024-03-26 18:15:47', '2024-03-26 18:15:47'),
