(621, NULL, 124, 1, '<p>A sector has an arc length \\(l\\) of \\(3.5 \\pi \\mathrm{cm}\\) and an area \\(A\\) of \\(36 \\pi \\mathrm{cm}^2\\). The radius of the sector is given as \\(r \\mathrm{~cm}\\).</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">Hence, find the central angle, \\(\\theta\\), of the sector in exact form</p>', 'Quiz', 5, 29, 131, '<p>Considering formulas for arc length and sector area: $$ \\begin{gathered} l=r \\theta \\\\ A=\\frac{1}{2} r^2 \\theta \\\\ \\therefore r \\theta=3.5 \\pi(1) \\\\ \\therefore \\frac{1}{2} r^2 \\theta=36 \\pi(2) \\end{gathered} $$Hence, solving simultaneously: $$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\frac{1}{2} r^2 \\theta=36 \\pi \\\\ &amp; \\frac{1}{2} r \\times r \\theta=36 \\pi \\\\ &amp; \\frac{1}{2} r \\times(3.5 \\pi)=36 \\pi[\\text { Substituting equation (1)] } \\\\ &amp; r=\\frac{36 \\pi}{3.5 \\pi} \\times 2 \\\\ &amp; \\therefore r=\\frac{144}{7} \\mathrm{~cm} \\end{aligned} $$Since \\(r=\\frac{144}{7}\\), from equation 1: $$ \\frac{144}{7} \\theta=3.5 \\pi $$$$ \\begin{aligned} \\therefore \\theta &amp; =3.5 \\pi \\times \\frac{7}{144} \\\\ &amp; =\\frac{49}{288} \\pi \\end{aligned} $$</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>\\(\\theta=\\frac{21}{37}\\pi\\)</p>', '300', 'Medium', '3', 1, NULL, '2024-03-26 18:24:35', '2024-03-26 18:24:35'),
