(633, NULL, 126, 1, '<p>A circle has centre \\(\\mathrm{O}\\) and a radius of \\(14 \\mathrm{~cm}\\). A chord \\(\\mathrm{AB}\\) of the circle is drawn, making triangle \\(A O B\\) an equilateral triangle.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img src=\"https://lwfiles.mycourse.app/63869eb3262971b3f737797c-public/8737ef90cc98b7c1bf8664d121ad3067.jpeg\" style=\"height:277px; width:359px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>i. State in radians, the size of angle AOB&nbsp;<br />\r\n[1 mark]</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ii. Calculate the area of the minor segment&nbsp;<br />\r\n[3 marks]</p>', 'Quiz', 5, 29, 131, '<p>i. Since we know \\(\\triangle A O B\\) is equilateral: $$ \\therefore \\angle A O B=\\frac{\\pi}{3} $$</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ii. For the area of a minor segment: $$ \\begin{aligned} \\text { Area } &amp; =\\text { Area of Sector }- \\text { Area of } \\triangle A O B \\\\ &amp; =\\frac{1}{2} r^2 \\theta-\\frac{1}{2} r^2 \\sin \\theta \\\\ &amp; =\\frac{1}{2} r^2(\\theta-\\sin \\theta) \\\\ &amp; =\\frac{1}{2}(14)^2\\left(\\frac{\\pi}{3}-\\sin \\frac{\\pi}{3}\\right) \\\\ &amp; =\\frac{1}{2}(196)\\left(\\frac{\\pi}{3}-\\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2}\\right) \\\\ &amp; =98\\left(\\frac{\\pi}{3}-\\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2}\\right) \\mathrm{cm}^2 \\end{aligned} $$ Must give your answer in exact values!</p>', 'correct', '<p>part i:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>$$\\frac{\\pi}{3}$$</p>\r\n\r\n<p>part ii:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>$$\\text{Area }=98\\left(\\frac{\\pi}{3}-\\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2}\\right) \\mathrm{cm}^2$$</p>', '420', 'Medium', '4', 1, NULL, '2024-03-26 18:30:15', '2024-03-26 18:30:15'),
