(694, NULL, 139, 1, '<p>$$ \\text {Solve } \\sin \\left(\\frac{x}{2}-\\frac{\\pi}{4}\\right)=\\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2} \\text { for } 0 \\leq x \\leq 2 \\pi $$</p>', 'Quiz', 5, 29, 133, '<p>Considering the domain restriction:$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; 0 \\leq x \\leq 2 \\pi \\\\ &amp; 0 \\leq \\frac{x}{2} \\leq \\pi \\\\ &amp; -\\frac{\\pi}{4} \\leq \\frac{x}{2}-\\frac{\\pi}{4} \\leq \\frac{3 \\pi}{4} \\end{aligned} $$Since \\(\\sin \\frac{\\pi}{3}=\\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2}\\):$$<br />\r\n\\therefore \\frac{x}{2}-\\frac{\\pi}{4}=\\frac{\\pi}{3} \\text { OR } \\pi-\\frac{\\pi}{3}[\\sin \\theta&gt;0 \\text { in } 1 s t, 2 \\text { nd quadrant }]<br />\r\n$$$$<br />\r\n\\frac{x}{2}-\\frac{\\pi}{4}=\\frac{\\pi}{3} \\text { OR } \\frac{2 \\pi}{3}<br />\r\n$$$$<br />\r\n\\begin{aligned}<br />\r\n&amp; \\frac{x}{2}=\\frac{\\pi}{3}+\\frac{\\pi}{4} \\text { OR } \\frac{2 \\pi}{3}+\\frac{\\pi}{4} \\\\<br />\r\n&amp; \\frac{x}{2}=\\frac{7 \\pi}{12} \\text { OR } \\frac{11 \\pi}{12}<br />\r\n\\end{aligned}<br />\r\n$$$$<br />\r\n\\begin{aligned}<br />\r\n\\therefore x &amp; =\\frac{14 \\pi}{12} \\text { oR } \\frac{22 \\pi}{12} \\\\<br />\r\n&amp; =\\frac{7 \\pi}{6} \\text { oR } \\frac{11 \\pi}{6}<br />\r\n\\end{aligned}<br />\r\n$$</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>\\(x=\\frac{\\pi}{6}\\text{ OR }\\frac{5\\pi}{6}\\)</p>', '300', 'Hard', '3', 1, NULL, '2024-03-26 20:40:17', '2024-03-26 20:40:17'),
