(714, NULL, 142, 1, '<p>Solve the equation \\(\\operatorname{cosec} \\theta+6 \\sin \\theta=5\\) for \\(0 \\leq \\theta \\leq 2 \\pi\\), giving your answer in radians and correct to the nearest 2 decimal places if necessary</p>', 'Quiz', 5, 29, 133, '<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\operatorname{cosec} \\theta+6 \\sin \\theta=5 \\\\ &amp; \\frac{1}{\\sin \\theta}+6 \\sin \\theta=5 \\\\ &amp; \\frac{1+6 \\sin ^2 \\theta}{\\sin \\theta}-5=0 \\\\ &amp; \\frac{1+6 \\sin ^2 \\theta-5 \\sin \\theta}{\\sin \\theta}=0 \\\\ &amp; \\therefore 6 \\sin ^2 \\theta-5 \\sin \\theta+1=0 \\end{aligned} $$Solving using the quadratic formula: $$ \\begin{aligned} \\sin \\theta &amp; =\\frac{5 \\pm \\sqrt{(-5)^2-4(6)(1)}}{2(6)} \\\\ &amp; =\\frac{5 \\pm \\sqrt{1}}{12} \\\\ &amp; =\\frac{5 \\pm 1}{12} \\\\ &amp; =\\frac{1}{2} \\text { OR } \\frac{1}{3} \\end{aligned} $$For \\(\\sin \\theta=\\frac{1}{2}\\): $$ \\therefore \\theta=\\frac{\\pi}{6} \\text { OR } \\frac{5 \\pi}{6} $$ For \\(\\sin \\theta=\\frac{1}{3}\\): $$ \\begin{aligned} \\therefore \\theta &amp; =0.34 \\text { OR } \\pi-0.34 \\\\ &amp; =0.34 \\text { OR } 2.80 \\end{aligned} $$</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>\\(\\theta=\\frac{\\pi}{3},\\frac{2\\pi}{3},0.43\\text{ OR }2.71\\)</p>', '420', 'Medium', '4', 1, NULL, '2024-03-26 20:47:40', '2024-03-26 20:47:40'),
