(736, NULL, 145, 1, '<p>A horizontal bridge is built between the points A and B. The bridge has multiply vertical pylons, one of which is ST and supported by cables SP and SR which are attached to its top.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img src=\"https://lwfiles.mycourse.app/63869eb3262971b3f737797c-public/4a8c893a4969ff8ec92d010cc5d0a7da.png\" style=\"height:207px; width:500px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The section of the pylon, SQ which is above the bridge is \\(11 \\mathrm{~m}\\) long and \\(\\angle S R Q=58^{\\circ}\\). The distance \\(\\mathrm{AQ}\\) is \\(26 \\mathrm{~m}\\), and \\(P\\) is the midpoint of \\(\\mathrm{AQ}\\)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>i. Find the length of the cable SR to the nearest metre&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>[1 mark]</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ii. Find the size of \\(\\angle S P Q\\) to the nearest minute&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>[2 marks]</p>', 'Both', 5, 29, 134, '<p>i. Considering \\(\\triangle S Q R\\):</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img src=\"https://lwfiles.mycourse.app/63869eb3262971b3f737797c-public/5596ec3a78b7d2e47429ae6deda113fb.jpeg\" style=\"height:315px; width:270px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\sin 52^{\\circ}=\\frac{11}{S R} \\\\ &amp; S R=\\frac{11}{\\sin 52^{\\circ}} \\\\ &amp; \\therefore S R \\approx 14 m \\text { [nearest metre] } \\end{aligned} $$</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ii. Since \\(\\mathrm{P}\\) is the midpoint of \\(\\mathrm{AQ}\\), then \\(P Q=\\frac{26}{2}=13 \\mathrm{~m}\\)&nbsp;<br />\r\nHence, considering \\(\\triangle S P Q\\):</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img src=\"https://lwfiles.mycourse.app/63869eb3262971b3f737797c-public/3d57b24f287b0ce4bd6b8c8cd4dbc404.jpeg\" style=\"height:239px; width:354px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\tan x^{\\circ}=\\frac{11}{13} \\\\ &amp; \\therefore x \\approx 40^{\\circ} 14^{\\prime \\prime} \\end{aligned} $$ Hence, the size of \\(\\angle S P Q\\) is \\(40^{\\circ} 14^{\\prime \\prime}\\)</p>', 'correct', '<p>part i:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>$$SR=1