(789, NULL, 153, 1, '<p><strong>This question continues from the previous part. You may use your previous answer to complete this part.&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Alberto stands at a point A, \\(150 \\mathrm{~m}\\)&nbsp;east of the tower OT which stands at a height of \\(h\\)&nbsp;metres. The angle of elevation of \\(\\mathrm{T}\\)&nbsp;from point \\(\\mathrm{A}\\)&nbsp;is \\(20^{\\circ}\\). Ben stands at point \\(\\mathrm{B}\\), due south of the tower OT. The angle of elevation to the top of the tower from B is \\(12^{\\circ}\\).</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img src=\"https://lwfiles.mycourse.app/63869eb3262971b3f737797c-public/1ad351be433241e44eee5b224aea225b.png\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>iii. What is the bearing of Ben from Alberto? Give your answer to the nearest minute</p>', 'Quiz', 5, 29, 135, '<p>iii. Drawing line \\(\\mathrm{AN}\\)&nbsp;to represent the North direction on the diagram:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img src=\"https://lwfiles.mycourse.app/63869eb3262971b3f737797c-public/81ce88a9e116e93559226ddf00787e03.png\" style=\"height:408px; width:500px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Now consider \\(\\triangle A B O\\):</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To find \\(\\angle A B O\\):$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\tan \\angle A B O=\\frac{150}{241} \\\\ &amp; \\therefore \\angle A B O \\approx 31^{\\circ} 54^{\\prime} \\end{aligned} $$ Hence, since \\(\\mathrm{BO}\\)&nbsp;and \\(\\mathrm{AN}\\)&nbsp;are parallel lines: $$ \\begin{aligned} \\angle B A N &amp; =180^{\\circ}-\\angle A B O \\\\ &amp; =180^{\\circ}-31^{\\circ} 54^{\\prime} \\\\ &amp; =148^{\\circ} 6^{\\prime} \\end{aligned} $$ Therefore, the bearing of point B from A will be: $$ 360^{\\circ}-148^{\\circ} 6=211^{\\circ} 54^{\\prime} \\mathrm{T} $$</p>', 'incorrect', '<p>\\(243^{\\circ} 31^{\\prime}\\)</p>', '180', 'Medium', '2', 1, NULL, '2024-03-27 19:22:16', '2024-03-27 19:22:16'),
